{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a934f485-12d5-4f83-88e7-7a2f015c0e45","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2** / .NET 9, so you can use the modern patterns:\n\n- **`TestContext`** — inject via **constructor** (no more static property).\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — supports `async Task` directly.\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service = null!;\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        // Sync init: constructor injection for TestContext\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // Async init runs before each test\n        _service = await MyService.CreateAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        var result = await _service.DoWorkAsync();\n        Assert.IsNotNull(result);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** handles sync setup + `TestContext` injection.\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** handles async setup (called before each test).\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** / **`[ClassCleanup]`** are also available for one-time async class-level setup if needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1400ad37-08fb-4cda-b281-cd1048bdd129","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use constructor injection (`TestContext` as a constructor parameter) rather than the legacy static property pattern.\n2. **Sync initialization**: `[TestInitialize]` method.\n3. **Async initialization**: `[TestInitialize]` supports `async Task` return type in MSTest v3.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer with the modern pattern.","outputTokens":458,"requestId":"082E:E43FA:DA7423:FBFBC3:69EAC73F"},"id":"9fa3e1fb-106f-40ad-a3a3-a40a1296c48c","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:28:41.542Z","parentId":"e1a625d4-3c55-44db-a958-d6b0ac111c24"}
